added.description: Tired of taking verbal abuse from his bandmate, Toki writes a tell-all book called Skwisgaar Is Ams Dick and takes over as Dethklok's lead guitarist.  But can Toki handle the spotlight? Meanwhile, Nathan buys a new favorite toy for the band: a defibrillator.

added.description: When Tommy mistakes a little person as a child his own age, he gets caught up in a big crime.

added.description: This loose parody of Stanley Kubrick's "2001: A Space Odyssey" features Joel Hodgson, creator of "Mystery Science Theater 3000," and comedic magicians Penn and Teller. Moltar and Zorak are fired when Space Ghost replaces them with MOE 2000, an unfeeling computer director.

Space Ghost introduces "Space Time Quiz Fun 9000" and his "contestants," comedians David Cross and Bob Odenkirk of HBO's "Mr. Show." What follows is a rapid-fire conversation in more ways than one, as Odenkirk's growing addiction to power-band blasts results in a steady volley from Space Ghost.
added.title: Gallagher
tags: space ghost coast to coast episode 35 gallagher bob odenkirk david cross mr show

added.description: Space Ghost loses the show to the owner of a liquor store, and he is forced to use a shark as the show's new mascot.  A bear wanders onto the set, upsetting the normal routine by repeatedly attacking Space Ghost.  Later, the shark explodes, attracting giant Space Bees.
added.title: Kentucky Nightmare
tags: space ghost c2c episode 77 kentucky nightmare

added.description: Space Ghost shows off his versatility by emceeing Cartoon Network's "World Premiere Toon In".  Members of the Council of Doom appear as judges in a beauty pageant-style competition between five cartoon directors. Blip also makes an appearance, prompting Space Ghost to croon, "Oh, what a monkey he is!"
